folder: West Street & Leroy Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
(1)
West Street, east side, from opposite Pier 36, North River, to Leroy Street, opposite Pier 41. The buildings being demolished at the right are on the north side of Charlton Street, which is to be closed west of Washington Street.
November 8, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same scene a little over a year later, before work really begins on the new St. John's Park Freight Terminal. The lamp post at the right of the 1930 view appears in this view
as the nearest one on the left.
January 18, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
